HEADWORD: deputize
<hw>dep"u*tize</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧p"⟦usl⟧*t⟦imac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<def>To appoint as one's deputy; to empower to act in one's stead; to
appoint as one's substitute; to depute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>deputy</ent>⟦br⟧
